From: dct-quantization project <dct-quantization@local>
Subject: [PATCH 05/XX] quantize: add --eoq and --eoq-compress flags for EOQ transport compression
Date: 2026-03-28

Add EOQ (Entropy-Optimized Quantization) transport compression as an
optional post-processing step in the llama-quantize tool.

Two usage modes:

  1. Quantize-and-compress in one step:
       ./llama-quantize model.gguf model-eoq.gguf Q4_K_M --eoq

     This performs standard quantization to Q4_K_M, then applies rANS
     entropy coding to each quantized tensor before writing the GGUF.

  2. Compress an already-quantized GGUF:
       ./llama-quantize model-q4.gguf model-eoq.gguf --eoq-compress

     This reads an existing quantized GGUF and applies rANS compression
     to every eligible tensor, producing an EOQ-compressed GGUF.

In both modes the output file contains tensors with type GGML_TYPE_EOQ.
Each tensor blob stores an eoq_tensor_header_t followed by the per-tensor
frequency table and rANS-encoded data.  At load time, the EOQ decode path
(added in patches 01-03) recovers the original quant blocks with zero
quality loss.

File-level GGUF metadata keys added:
  - general.file_type        = GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_EOQ
  - eoq.version              = 1
  - eoq.precision_bits       = 14  (configurable via --eoq-precision)
  - eoq.rans_block_size      = 4096 (configurable via --eoq-block-size)
  - eoq.original_ftype       = <the underlying quantization ftype>

---
 tools/quantize/quantize.cpp      |  ~90 lines added
 src/llama-quant.cpp               | ~180 lines added
 include/llama.h                   |   ~5 lines added
 3 files changed, ~275 insertions(+)

NOTE: This is a descriptive pseudo-code patch. The exact line numbers
depend on the version of llama.cpp you are patching against. The context
lines show the surrounding code to locate each hunk. Adjust offsets as
needed for your checkout.

Base reference: ggml-org/llama.cpp with EOQ type system patches 01-04
already applied (GGML_TYPE_EOQ = 43, GGML_FTYPE_MOSTLY_EOQ = 29).

Requires: eoq_rans_v2.h / eoq_rans_v2.c linked into the build (patch 04).

